cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.GT, cs.LG, cs.NI

This paper discusses the security of a consensus protocol used in cryptocurrencies, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also involves optimization of strategies, which could be categorized under distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). Game theory (cs.GT) is also mentioned as a tool for analyzing the attackers' strategies. Machine learning (cs.LG) could be relevant for analyzing the data and making predictions. Finally, network and internet architecture (cs.NI) could be relevant for understanding the structure of the cryptocurrency network.
